    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'd say leave it for 3.1, since CSS fixes seem to have a high probability of introducing new CSS bugs*. But Min understands this stuff better than I do, so I'll let him make the call.\n- CSS critical mass: the amount of CSS wherein each bugfix occasions, on average, >1 new problem, leading to an exponential increase in bugs.\n\n![250px-castle_romeo](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/327925/6382866/3198968c-bd01-11e4-922f-e0c60994463f.jpg)\n"
  },
